Folded the near-duplicate **grouping** stage into the #486 auto-pool calibration (completes #526). The scan now measures the grouping micro-rates (brute per-pair vs BK-tree per-candidate) alongside the hash thread/process timing, caches them under the same per-machine fingerprint, and derives the BK-tree crossover floor empirically instead of from a baked constant — so the grouping strategy self-tunes if a future hash recipe shifts the economics. The calibration fingerprint now also folds in `HASH_RECIPE_VERSION` (`scanner/hasher.py`) and `GROUPING_STRATEGY_VERSION` (`scanner/dedup.py`), so a cached calibration is correctly invalidated when the hash recipe or grouping strategy changes — closing the #517 breadcrumb where adding dHash to the hash tuple never invalidated the cache. ([#526](https://github.com/jackal998/photo-manager/issues/526))
